				 Kanoria in pact with Italian hotelier
 GARIMA SINGH NEOGY 																								New Delhi, Nov. 7: Shrishti Hotels, part of the Kanoria group, has entered into a 50:50 joint venture with Italian hotel chain Domina Group for management of 25 new hotels in India.																								According to the agreement, both partners will control the management of assets, while Shrishti will look after real estate development.																								The joint venture is expected to make an investment of around Rs 2,400 crore till 2012. The plan is to build four-star hotels and resorts having 100-200 rooms. 																								To be branded as Vedic Domina Hotels and Resorts, the entities will be set up in cities such as Calcutta, Delhi, Mumbai, Puri, Hyderabad, Bangalore and Udaipur and other holiday resorts.																								We are proud to announce the expansion of our group in India, said Ernesto Preatoni, chairman of Domina Group. 																								We are the first Italian company to enter the Indian hotel sector, Preatoni added.																								The first hotel is already under construction, and the others are also expected to open their doors in the next five years.																								Founded in 2000, the Italian hotel group has both business and leisure properties. Globally, the group is represented by three big brands  Domina Prestige, Domina Hotel and Domina Inn.
